outputs.output_descr:
The Community Empowerment and Development Project (CEDP) was originally designed as part of a post-conflict recovery programme. The programme was developed to be an integrated approach to post-conflict peace building to address the causes and consequences of the conflict. It focused on three main areas: a). National Recovery and Peace-building, b).Poverty Reduction and Human Development and c). Governance and Democratic Development.
The project has completed thirty-one (31) of the thirty-six (36) projects. The remaining projects are listed below:
1.	Rehabilitation of 18.4 Km Boroma/Gbangadu Road, Kono District;
2.	Proposed construction of ten (10) twin box culverts, two (02) pipe culverts, one (01) bridge along Boroma/Gbangadu road, Kono district;
3.	Proposed construction of market stalls at kabala Central market;
4.	Proposed construction of Lorry Park, Kailahun town; and
5.	Rehabilitation of gravity water system, Mapaki, Bombali district
